  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is Wednesday March 6, 1996.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm Michael Kuelker, interviewing Renate Vambery in St.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Louis, Missouri.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I studied occupational therapy on a full scholarship at Washington University from beginning of '38-- they gave me some credit for my schooling in-- in Switzerland-- psychology and education and things like that.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And graduated in 1940.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That is, I still had to do what we called clinical field work or an internship.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And was not-- I couldn't become a registered occupational therapist until 1941, but I was, for all practical purposes, had my degree from Wash U by that time-- from Washington University.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my first job, first I was then as a student to a state hospital in Nebraska and they then asked me to stay on a job there to direct the men's workshop, which I did.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then I-- I didn't want to stay in Nebraska.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I thought it was the end of the road, practically.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was-- was pretty desolate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, I-- we used to take the patients outside and we did recreational therapy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I have a little vignette to tell about that when one of the patients, great big-- most them were farmers.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He was a great big man named Ashley-- he was very nice looking, I remember.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he started to run away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were told if you lose a patient you lose your job.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I ran after him through the cornfield, and when I finally caught up-- it was a very hot summer day-- he said to me he would come back if I gave him a kiss or allowed him to kiss me.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said-- I was a student, and I said, OK, because I wanted to get him back.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
